# lj/cut/coul/esp correctness test (Step 4: pair_lj_cut_coul_esp_omp verification)
# PairLJCutCoulEsp : public Pair (KSPACE package). Standard lj/cut LJ term
# (cutsq/cut_ljsq/lj1-4/offset, per itype/jtype) combined with the same
# coul/esp Coulomb term ported in pair_coul_esp_omp.cpp: direct branch is an
# 11-term Horner polynomial (force_poly_coeff/energy_poly_coeff from the ESP
# kspace object) for rsq <= tabinnersq, table-lookup branch (ncoultablebits
# default = 12, tabinner = sqrt(2) -> tabinnersq = 2.0) otherwise. No `scale`
# array in this style (unlike coul/esp), so ecoul table branch has no scale
# multiplier. cut_lj = cut_coul = 4.0 (+0.3 skin = 4.3 < L/2 = 5.04 with this
# box) keeps neighbor distances spanning both sides of tabinnersq=2.0.

